Citations
Date:  0/0/1958
Source:  Sheep.  Part 1, Sheep husbandry
Author:  STEVENS
Vol / Page:  37
Edition:
Quote:  Shepherds speak of good tupping weather, but more often of bad tupping weather, when, because of extreme heat or heavy rain, the rams lose interest and many heat periods pass neglected.
